Depends: whiptail, {{ DEPS }}
Description: interactive first-boot user account setup wizard
 Provides a terminal TUI wizard that runs on the very first boot of a
 bootc-deployed system, before the login prompt appears. Guides the
 administrator through hostname configuration, locale and keyboard
 selection, primary user account creation, root password setup, sudo
 grant, and SSH root login policy.
 .
 Modelled after the Raspberry Pi OS userconfig service. Runs as an
 ExecStartPre hook on getty@tty1.service and leaves a completion flag
 at /var/lib/firstboot-user-setup.done to prevent re-execution on
 subsequent boots.
